The paper discusses the scalability issue of machine learning algorithms in learning logic programs, specifically Inductive Logic Programming algorithms. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of datasets for question answering (bAbl) and handwritten digit recognition (MNIST), which are commonly used in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) respectively. Additionally, the paper discusses the usability of knowledge representation and reasoning techniques, which falls under the category of Databases (cs.DB) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
